  <span id="freeText5608517369919642021" style="display:none">If you ever thought it was easy to make a movie, this book tells the inside scoop about all the little details that go on. Why all the credits at the ends of movies? This book is full of information about all those titles. A movie maker is telling the 26 year-old story of a suspected suicide. However, he uncovers some information that make it questionable whether this was a suicide or murder. Then the people involved so many years ago start a series of events designed to stop the movie so that the real truth won't come out. Very entertaining.</span>
