<div id="review_750778801" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/750778801" />
    <a title="Ann" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23554612-ann"><img alt="Ann" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1382754192p2/23554612.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/750778801?book_show_action=true">Oct 27, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ann" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ann" href="/user/show/23554612-ann">Ann</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780399139741" href="/book/show/2370121.Wild_Horses">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer750778801" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7004667974584952527">Still my favorite author of all time. Even after all these years (25 +) Dick Francis can still make me feel like I&apos;m part of the story. The plot &amp; characters pull you in and that&apos;s where you stay until the ride is over (when you have read the last word.) I always want to immediately read the sequel. Alas, there are few books written by Dick Francis that have sequels. This particular book grabbed me &amp; until I finished. The mystery solved. But what I wouldn&apos;t give to see the movie on the big scree</span>
  <span id="freeText7004667974584952527" style="display:none">Still my favorite author of all time. Even after all these years (25 +) Dick Francis can still make me feel like I'm part of the story. The plot &amp; characters pull you in and that's where you stay until the ride is over (when you have read the last word.) I always want to immediately read the sequel. Alas, there are few books written by Dick Francis that have sequels. This particular book grabbed me &amp; until I finished. The mystery solved. But what I wouldn't give to see the movie on the big screen! But only if is filmed EXACTLY how it was written in the book! LOL.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7004667974584952527" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
