        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1590363064" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16441032174818827482">It&apos;s been a long time since I read a Dick Francis book, but I&apos;m glad I picked up this one. It&apos;s not a horse book, exactly, in that the hero isn&apos;t a jockey but a film director making a Hollywood film about a racing-connected unsolved death 26 years ago. The insights into the film-making world are worth the price of the book alone, but the hook is the interpersonal here, the relationships between director and writer, director and producer, director and star, plus the non-film relationships that co</span>
  <span id="freeText16441032174818827482" style="display:none">It's been a long time since I read a Dick Francis book, but I'm glad I picked up this one. It's not a horse book, exactly, in that the hero isn't a jockey but a film director making a Hollywood film about a racing-connected unsolved death 26 years ago. The insights into the film-making world are worth the price of the book alone, but the hook is the interpersonal here, the relationships between director and writer, director and producer, director and star, plus the non-film relationships that connect us to the long-buried mystery.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16441032174818827482" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
